Rest in paradise Leah Nicole Brown 🙏🏼❤️

Leah was my best friend through highschool and early adulthood. My first roommate, My first real bond as an adult. She was very headstrong, responsible, smart, trustworthy, loyal and extremely motivated and ambitious. She owned her own home, two businesses and she was an amazing mother to her young son Carter. Some of the best memories of my life are right by her side. We really grew up together! My first trip to south beach partying was with her, my first time out of the country, my first time smoking weed, first big road trip in my mom’s truck and we were lost for hours lol, baking ur famous peanut butter and hershey cookies together for the holidays, we even went through a shootout and she helped me pick up the pieces after my boyfriend house got raided. We were truly ride or dies rolling through the Shaq blasting jeezy and boosie smoking dutches thinkin we were trap queens lol. Remember Christmas night 2007 when we saw the crazy meteor shower outside your house? Sundays we used to spend at her afterschool job and we would write down our dreams of getting out of that small town together. I always knew she would be successful. I’m so proud of her and all she accomplished in her life. She was a real friend that would tell the truth and help you realize your worth, she inspired me to be better. She didn’t take any shit she will say it like it is! Leah was a woman of her word and one of the best people I’ve ever met, we truly connected instantly, I still remember the day I met her. I’m so sad we drifted apart the last few years just living in different cities and moving on with life but the love I have for her is infinite. I’m still in shock. And this is a wake up call to live life to the fullest, be the best person you can and don’t let ppl you love drift away- tell the ppl you love that u love them NOW. U never know when it’s your last day. Rest in Peace and Love!!! ♾️

God First. Student of Life.
